Fresno.Lone Star, Fresno County, California:
Lone Star (formerly, Lonestar) is an unincorporated community in Fresno County, California. It is located on the Atchison, Topeka and Santa Fe Railroad 3.25 miles (5 km) east-northeast of Malaga, at an elevation of 318 feet (97 m).
The Lonestar post office operated from 1891 to 1895 and from 1900 to 1910.
